# Online resources and datasets


NOAA Climate.gov - www.climate.gov/teaching - Contains resources specifically designed for teaching, and other datasets

Kaggle - www.kaggle.com/datasets - Provides access to open datasets.Currently 41 datasets avaiable with keywords "Climate Change"

Github - www.github.com/awesomedata/awesome-public-datasets - Currently 18 open datasets listed relating to Climate and Weather

Stanford Hurricane Irma tracker assignment - http://nifty.stanford.edu/2018/ventura-hurricane-tracker/irma-assignment.html

NASA EarthData - https://earthdata.nasa.gov/earth-observation-data/visualize-data - Provides satellite imagery and visualisations of realtime and historic data on fires, weather, temperatures etc.

Global ForestWatch - https://www.globalforestwatch.org/howto/tags/odp/ - Provides data of deforestation and forest fires.

NOAA Climate data online - https://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/cdo-web/datasets - Online repository for climate data

NASA Climate Education Resources - www.climate.nasa.gov/resources/education/ - Resources for educators teaching Climate Change

IPCC Data Distribution Centre - www.ipcc-data.org - Data designed for Climate Change researchers and educators

WWF Wildlife and Climate Change Educator Resources - https://www.worldwildlife.org/pages/wildlife-and-climate-change-educator-resources

National Science Teaching Association - www.nsta.org/climate - Lots of links to relevant ideas and datasets - WE SHOULD EXPLORE & INCLUDE SOME!
